Use sqlcmd (SQL Server command-line tool) to import the database schema.
Do NOT use Python scripts for SQL execution.

sqlcmd supports GO batch separators natively and uses Azure AD authentication with the -G flag.

Add the following commands to deploy-infra/README.md for Step 6 (Import Database Schema):

```powershell
$sqlServerName = (az deployment group show --resource-group $resourceGroup --name main --query "properties.outputs.sqlServerName.value" -o tsv)

# Using sqlcmd with Azure AD authentication (handles GO statements natively)
sqlcmd -S "$sqlServerName.database.windows.net" -d "Northwind" -G -i "Database-Schema/database_schema.sql"
```

If the user doesn't have sqlcmd installed, provide installation instructions:

```powershell
# Windows (via winget)
winget install Microsoft.SqlCmd

# macOS (via Homebrew)
brew install sqlcmd

# Linux (Debian/Ubuntu)
curl https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | sudo apt-key add -
curl https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/$(lsb_release -rs)/prod.list | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/msprod.list
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install mssql-tools18
```

The -G flag enables Azure Active Directory authentication using the currently logged-in Azure CLI credentials.


